Nice, do you know Donald Trump

Donald Trump is a well-known American businessman, politician, and the 45th President of the United States. He served from 2017 to 2021. Before his presidency, he was a reality TV star, with appearances on the show "The Apprentice" and its spin-off "The Celebrity Apprentice."

Trump's business career spanned decades and included real estate development, construction, and branding. He built his empire through his family's real estate company, The Trump Organization, which handled various projects, including high-end hotels, golf courses, and residential developments.

As a politician, Trump ran for the Republican nomination in 2016 and won, going on to defeat Democratic candidate Hillary Clinton in the general election. During his presidency, he implemented policies aimed at reducing regulations, cutting taxes, and reforming healthcare. However, his tenure was also marked by controversy, including accusations of collusion with Russia during the 2016 presidential campaign.

After leaving office, Trump has remained a prominent public figure, continuing to speak out on politics and issues through social media, rallies, and other means. His views often spark debate and discussion, both within the United States and internationally.
